Date: 19/7/1841
Source: GBPP
Author:
Vol / Page: 134
Edition:
Quote: From the extreme value of allotments with water frontages for commercial people, the [Auckland] waterside was subdivided into very small allotments ... but two of the best of these [allotments], bordering on a fresh-water creek, which runs down through the valley, have been selected by Government officers.
Notes: D. Sinclair to Lord John Russell in GBPP 1842 (No.569)

